description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;BARNSLEY HOSPITAL NHS FOUNDATION TRUST&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;LOCUM APPOINTMENT FOR SERVICE (HIGHER)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;ACUTE MEDICINE / CARE OF THE ELDERLY&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;ST3+ LEVEL&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;This is not a training post&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;£32,478 - £51,069&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Applications are invited from enthusiastic and capable doctors for the above post at ST3+ level in Acute Medicine and Care of the Elderly within Barnsley Hospital NHS Foundation Trust. The post does not attract educational approval from Health Education England, but the successful candidate will have the opportunity to participate in local teaching/ training.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The successful applicant will be appointed to this post on a fixed term contract. Working in Acute Medicine from 2&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;nd&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt; December 2020 until 6&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;th&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt; April 2021 and Care of the Elderly from 7&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;th&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt; April 2021 until 3&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;rd&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt; August 2021.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Barnsley Hospital NHS Foundation Trust is a ‘Good’ CQC-rated Hospital with a vision to moving to “Outstanding” and joining only 7 other hospitals in the country with this rating.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Informal enquiries and visits are welcomed by direct contact with Dr Fraz Ahmed, Consultant and Dr Bahaa Madi, Consultant.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;This post offers:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Excellent experience of Acute and Elderly Medicine in a DGH setting&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Support from experienced middle grade doctors working a full shift system.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Full consultant cover readily available&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ward and outpatient Phlebotomy service&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Opportunity to experience Acute Medical Assessment Clinic (Ambulatory Care)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Regular weekly commitment to three one-hour educational sessions with a programme developed to meet the needs of all trainees&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;On site PGME and library facilities&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Regular appraisal and Performance Reviews&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Barnsley lies about 1 mile from the M1 Motorway, close to the cities of Leeds and Sheffield, with easy access to the Peak District, the Pennines and the Yorkshire Dales.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Barnsley Hospital NHS Foundation Trust is committed to promoting equality of opportunity and fair treatment to all applicants regardless of race, nationality, ethnic origin, gender, marital status, mental or physical disability, religion or belief, sexual orientation, age or offending history.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;PLEASE NOTE: all correspondence regarding this vacancy and the interview process will be sent by e-mail.  Therefore, you are advised to check your emails/NHS Jobs account regularly following the closing date.   To speed up the recruitment process please ensure that your references are appropriate and where possible you have provided an email address and telephone number.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Trust is committed to safeguarding adults and children therefore if the post is subject to the Rehabilitation of Offenders Act (ROA) 1974 (Exceptions) Order 1975 (as amended) the successful candidate(s) will be subject to a criminal records check with the Disclosure and Barring Service (DBS).  The cost of the DBS must be met by the successful candidate(s) through salary deduction. DBS charges for adverts placed from 1st June are as follows:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Standard Check:    £26.00 + Administration cost of £3.69 = deduction from salary as a one off payment&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Enhanced Check:  £44.00 + administration cost of £3.69 = £14.69 deduction from 1st month’s salary, £11.00 deduction from salary over following 3 months.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Please note that this advert will close once a sufficient number of applications have been received.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;If you wish to apply for this post, please visit NHS Jobs website and quote Ref No: 163-3573-11-20&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
